-- Cruzeiro, Embraer, Grana y Montero, Klabin: Latin America Equity Preview
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n   a n d   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2010-10-14T07:19:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/cruzeiro-embraer-grana-y-montero-klabin-latin-america-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in Latin American trading. Stock symbols
are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous close.  The  MSCI Latin America Index  rose 1.8 percent to 4,604.12.
In Brazil, preferred shares usually are the most-traded class of
stock.  Brazil  Banco Cruzeiro do Sul SA  (CZRS4 BS): Standard & Poor’s
assigned a BB-/B counterparty credit rating and a stable outlook
to the lender, reflecting the bank’s concentration in one type
of product and its profitability, according to a press release
distributed by the credit rating company. Banco Cruzeiro rose
1.2 percent to 14.88 reais.  Empresa Brasileira de Aeronautica SA  (EMBR3 BS): The
aeronautics company signed a pact with Air Lease Corp. for the
sale of up to 20 Embraer 190 aircraft, with first delivery to
take place in June 2011, according to a regulatory filing.
Embraer fell 4.2 percent to 11.56 reais.  Klabin SA  (KLBN4 BS): The paper producer said it will buy
as much as 45.3 million of its preferred shares, or the
equivalent to 10 percent of the total outstanding, during the
next 12 months, according to a regulatory filing. Klabin fell
0.6 percent to 4.75 reais.  Peru  Grana y Montero SA  (GRAMONC1 PE): The Lima-based
construction company will receive a $50 million loan from
Caracas-based lender Corporacion Andina de Fomento, known as CAF.
Grana y Montero rose 1.7 percent to 6.46 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
